    "question_id" : 8512121,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>You could use the methods described in this question (especially since you start off with an InputStream): <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/q/309424/372643\">Read/convert an InputStream to a String</a></p>\n\n<p>In particular, if you don't want to rely on external libraries, you can try <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/a/309718/372643\">this answer</a>, which reads the <code>InputStream</code> via an <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/6/docs/api/java/io/InputStreamReader.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>InputStreamReader</code></a> into a <code>char[]</code> buffer and appends it into a <code>StringBuilder</code>.</p>\n"
